        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 2:14AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 214 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Wheeler, or 20 miles north of Shamrock, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shamrock, Briscoe, Wheeler, New Mobeetie, Twitty, Allison, Lela,
Kellerville, and Mobeetie.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
